r"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "basedtyping", "documentation": ["The main `basedtyping` module. the types/functions defined here can be used at\nboth type-time and at runtime.\n"], "functions": [{"name": "basedtyping._type_convert", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arg", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["For converting None to type(None), and strings to ForwardRef.\n\nStolen from typing."]}, {"name": "basedtyping.issubform", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "form", "type": {"name": "_Forms", "xref": {"fqname": "_Forms", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "forminfo", "type": {"name": "_Forms", "xref": {"fqname": "_Forms", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["EXPERIMENTAL: Warning, this function currently only supports unions and `Never`.\n\nReturns `True` if `form` is a subform (specialform or subclass) of `forminfo`.\n\nLike `issubclass` but supports typeforms (type-time types)\n\nfor example:\n\n```pycon\n>>> issubclass(int | str, object)\nTypeError: issubclass() arg 1 must be a class\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> issubform(int | str, str)\nFalse\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> issubform(int | str, object)\nTrue\n```\n", "TODO: make this work with any \"form\", not just unions  # noqa: TD003", "should be (form: TypeForm, forminfo: TypeForm)", "TODO: form/forminfo can include _UnionGenericAlias  # noqa: TD003"]}, {"name": "basedtyping.Untyped", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": {"name": "_BasedSpecialForm", "xref": {"fqname": "basedtyping._BasedSpecialForm", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "parameters", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "NoReturn", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.NoReturn", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Special type indicating that something isn't typed.\n\nThis is more specialized than `Any` and can help with gradually typing modules.\n"]}, {"name": "basedtyping.Intersection", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": {"name": "_BasedSpecialForm", "xref": {"fqname": "basedtyping._BasedSpecialForm", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "parameters", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Intersection type; Intersection[X, Y] means both X and Y.\n\nTo define an intersection:\n\\- If using \\_\\_future\\_\\_.annotations, shortform can be used e.g. A & B\n\\- otherwise the fullform must be used e.g. Intersection[A, B].\n\nDetails:\n\\- The arguments must be types and there must be at least one.\n\\- None as an argument is a special case and is replaced by\n\n> type(None).\n\n- Intersections of intersections are flattened, e.g.:\n\n  ```\n  Intersection[Intersection[int, str], float] == Intersection[int, str, float]\n  ```\n\n- Intersections of a single argument vanish, e.g.:\n\n  ```\n  Intersection[int] == int  # The constructor actually returns int\n  ```\n\n- Redundant arguments are skipped, e.g.:\n\n  ```\n  Intersection[int, str, int] == Intersection[int, str]\n  ```\n\n- When comparing intersections, the argument order is ignored, e.g.:\n\n  ```\n  Intersection[int, str] == Intersection[str, int]\n  ```\n\n- You cannot subclass or instantiate an intersection.\n"]}, {"name": "basedtyping.as_functiontype", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fn", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "P", "xref": null, "params": null}, {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "FunctionType", "xref": {"fqname": "FunctionType", "project": null}, "params": [{"name": "P", "xref": {"fqname": "P", "project": null}, "params": null}, {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Asserts that a `Callable` is a `FunctionType` and returns it\n\nbest used as a decorator to fix other incorrectly typed decorators:\n\n> def deco(fn: Callable\\[[], None\\]) -> Callable\\[[], None\\]: ...\n>\n> @as_functiontype\n> @deco\n> def foo(): ...\n"]}, {"name": "basedtyping._type_check", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arg", "type": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "object", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.object", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Check that the argument is a type, and return it (internal helper).\n\nAs a special case, accept None and return type(None) instead. Also wrap strings\ninto ForwardRef instances. Consider several corner cases, for example plain\nspecial forms like Union are not valid, while Union[int, str] is OK, etc.\nThe msg argument is a human-readable error message, e.g:\n\n```\n\"Union[arg, ...]: arg should be a type.\"\n```\n\nWe append the repr() of the actual value (truncated to 100 chars).\n"]}, {"name": "basedtyping.get_type_hints", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "object\n    | Callable[..., object]\n    | FunctionType[..., object]\n    | types.BuiltinFunctionType[..., object]\n    | types.MethodType\n    | types.ModuleType\n    | types.WrapperDescriptor